Message.MsgText: WMQCLIENT_HEARTBEAT_FAILED_SICM0016=CWSIQ0016E: A WebSphere MQ client application failed to send a heartbeat flow over MQClientLink {0} in the specified heartbeatInterval {1}.
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ client application failed to send a heartbeat flow. It is possible that the client has terminated. The connection that was previously established with the client has been dropped.
Message.UserResponse: If the WebSphere MQ client has not been intentionally terminated, read the error logs to determine the cause of termination.

Message.MsgText: CONNIMPL_CLOSED_SICM0020=CWSIQ0020E: An operation was attempted on a connection that is already closed.
Message.Explanation: An operation was attempted on a connection resource that has previously been closed. This problem can result from an application programming error or because the system closed the connection resource in response to an error condition.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log files for your application server to determine why the connection closed. See the accompanying error messages for further information and correct the problem if possible.

Message.MsgText: CF_INIT_FAILED_SICM0007=CWSIQ0007E: The MQFAP channel failed to initialize because of previous errors.
Message.Explanation: This message indicates that previous problems prevent the initialization of the MQFAP channel, the exact problem preventing initialization of the channel may be indicated by previous error messages.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the error and FFDC logs to identify the cause of the problem.

Message.MsgText: CONNMGR_CONNFAILED_SICM0022=CWSIQ0022E: A network connection to host name {0}, port {1} using transport chain {2} cannot be established.
Message.Explanation: A networking error occurred when attempting to establish a connection to the specified host. See the linked exception for further details.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the specified host name is valid and that a process is listening for connections on the specified port.

Message.MsgText: SENDERCHL_NO_RECV_CHANNEL_SICM0018=CWSIQ0018E: The sender channel {0} for MQLink {1} has failed to establish a session with remote host {2} because the partner receiver channel is not available.
Message.Explanation: The specified sender channel for the specified MQ link could not establish a connection with the partner because the partner receiver channel is not available. It is possible that the receiver channel has not been defined or is in a STOPPED state.
Message.UserResponse: For further information on resolving this error, see the problem determination information on the Application Server Support Web page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support.

Message.MsgText: SENDERCHL_NO_LISTENER_SICM0017=CWSIQ0017E: The sender channel {0} for MQLink {1} has failed to establish a connection with the remote host {2} because the remote listener for port {3} is not available.
Message.Explanation: The specified sender channel for the specified MQ link could not establish a connection with the partner because a suitable listener is not available.
Message.UserResponse: For further information on resolving this error, see the problem determination information on the Application Server Support Web page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support.
